      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>Virginia architect Robert L. Auldridge's papers consist
         chiefly of his student drawings and sketches. The majority are
         charcoal studies of architectural details and perspectives,
         still lifes and the human figure.</p>
         <p>There are also watercolors of a family tree of the
         descendants of Josiah Beers and several proposed buildings
         including a Union Pacific railroad terminal, a summer art
         colony, a trade school and a dancing casino. The only
         identified building is of a school at Riverton, Warren County,
         Va.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement>
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Arranged chronologically and alphabetically by medium.</p>
      </arrangement>
